.TH "dma_alloc_from_contiguous" 9 "dma_alloc_from_contiguous" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_alloc_from_contiguous \- allocate pages from contiguous area
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct page *" dma_alloc_from_contiguous
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "size_t count "  ","
.BI "unsigned int align "  ","
.BI "bool no_warn "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
Pointer to device for which the allocation is performed.
.IP "count" 12
Requested number of pages.
.IP "align" 12
Requested alignment of pages (in PAGE_SIZE order).
.IP "no_warn" 12
Avoid printing message about failed allocation.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function allocates memory buffer for specified device. It uses
device specific contiguous memory area if available or the default
global one. Requires architecture specific \fBdev_get_cma_area\fP helper
function.
